The Romans often conferred the dis· tinction of citizenship upon foreigners who had been useful to them. In such cases, frequently the person honored became a client of the Roman through whom citizenship was bestowed, and adopted his gentile name. A. 80a3 H. 649. Thus Procillus took the name of Flaccus.
